1) the Python API for Apache Spark that allows you to write Spark applications using Python,PySpark is the Python API for Apache Spark that allows developers to 
write distributed data processing applications in Python. While Spark runs on the JVM, PySpark communicates with it using Py4J,
which introduces some overhead compared to native Scala Spark,but provides ease of use and integration with Python libraries

2) 🔹 1. Spark Core
👉 Foundation of everything
Handles:
Task scheduling
Memory management
Fault tolerance (lineage)
👉 All other components depend on this
🔹 2. Spark SQL
👉 For structured data processing
Works with:
DataFrames
SQL queries
Uses:
Catalyst Optimizer
Tungsten engine
👉 Most used in real data engineering jobs
🔹 3. Spark Streaming / Structured Streaming
👉 For real-time data processing
Processes data in micro-batches
Supports:
Kafka
File streams
👉 Used in real-time pipelines
🔹 4. MLlib (Machine Learning Library)
👉 Built-in ML library
Classification
Regression
Clustering
