🔹 5. GraphX
👉 Graph processing engine
Works with graph data
Nodes + edges
👉 Rarely used in typical DE roles

The Spark ecosystem consists of Spark Core for execution, Spark SQL for structured data processing, Structured Streaming for real-time processing,
MLlib for machine learning, and GraphX for graph processing. These components work together on top of Spark’s distributed architecture and integrate 
with storage systems and cluster managers


3) PySpark is faster than MapReduce because it processes data in memory and uses DAG-based execution instead of disk-heavy MapReduce stages. 
It also provides high-level APIs like DataFrames and supports both batch and streaming workloads,making it more flexible and efficient.
